message: Peter Deming replaced Mark Irwin a week prior to the end of principal photography, as stated in the 'Filming' sub-section.
Was unable to verify Wings Hauser story credit.
Actor William Kiehl recorded a new opening narration for the English-language release.

Roland Joffe is listed as an uncredited co-director on both his personal page and the film's IMDB. Original directors Morton and Jenkel were both fired partway through filming, producer Joffe took over and directed the lion's share of the film with Semler
To my understanding, Joffe has maintained his English citizenship and has spent the majority of his working career there. Therefore, I feel that 'English-French' is far more appropriate.
A Significant amount of The Reds' original soundtrack was replaced with music by the English rock band Shriekback, as mentioned later in the article.

Added 'scenes deleted' to the Another 48 Hrs credit. During post-production, a good chunk of the footage was cut to reduce the run-time, including almost all of McRae's scenes. In the final cut, he appears once, uncredited, as background extra.
